      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GRIPPING (3) found the frame two back at Warrnambool then again ran a good race to finish second last time out, beaten 4 lengths, in a hurdle at Hamilton. Will have taken great benefit from those jumps runs and this looks the easiest hurdle race he's been in. EMBEZZLER (2) is looking to improve on a last-start 13th on the flat over 2440m at Geelong on June 19. Much better suited here and looks a genuine threat. SHOGUN EXPRESS (7) unfortunately failed to finish on his jumps debut in a hurdle at Hamilton, but did start at $7 there so had obviously shown something and warrants another chance. HIGHNESS (4) needs to lift but should be nearing peak fitness now.",
